
X chatter is a Command Line chat utility . It can be used to communicate between a client and a server

The utility has two parts , 

1) Server part
2) Client Part


1) Server part , runs on the server machine

	compiling :
		javac -Xlint:deprecation Server.java
	running:
		java Server port_number nickname

	eg:
		java Server 8000 cobra

2) Client part , runs on any machine , and connect to server to start communication

	compiling:
		javac -Xling:deprecation Client.java 
	running:
		java Client machine server_port nickname

	eg:
		java localhost 8000 vijeen

once the connecion between the client and server is established then communicaion can be started .


